parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower ball joint can cause the wheel to separate from the vehicle, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The ball joint breaks or separates
causing the vehicle to drop to the ground
loss of control
and potential accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the upper ball joint can cause the vehicle to vibrate uncontrollably, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The upper ball joint fails
causing the vehicle to vibrate uncontrollably
and potential loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust corrosion of suspension components can cause the components to fail, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Rust corrosion of suspension components
such as the strut towers and control arm mounting points
leading to failure of the components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spindle (knuckle assembly) can cause loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The spindle (knuckle assembly) wears out or breaks
causing the vehicle to drift out of the lane and potential loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Denied Repair of Ball Joints under Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed or denied repair of ball joints under recall can cause the vehicle to be unsafe to drive, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: Dealers delay or deny repair of ball joints under recall
leaving the vehicle in an unsafe condition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause damage to other components, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: Transfer case noise
leaky transfer case
vehicle locks up
wheels lock up
loss of power
difficulty shifting gears
transmission failure.

symptoms: Transmission locks up
intermittent slippage
gears/transmission unable to engage
loud banging noise
vehicle stalls
difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and shutting off can cause loss of power, loss of control, and accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off while driving
often without warning
and may be accompanied by a loud noise or vibration. The vehicle may also experience difficulty starting or restarting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft thrust bearing can cause the engine to seize, leading to loss of power, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: The engine may experience excessive vibration
noise
or movement
and may eventually seize or shut off. The crankshaft position sensor may also be damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause engine overheating, oil leaks, and engine damage, leading to loss of power, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: The engine may experience overheating
oil leaks
or white smoke from the exhaust. The head gasket may also be blown
causing engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Leak and Engine Bearing Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine bearings can cause the engine to seize, leading to loss of power, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: The engine may experience oil leaks
excessive noise or vibration
and eventual seizure or shut off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbocharger can cause loss of power, loss of control, and accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine may experience loss of power
